Mirror Audit — Instruction

Purpose:
- Verify `test/` folder is fully mirrored by the scaffolder templates in `generate-file-structure.php`, identify missing/changed files, and produce actionable patches.

Prerequisites:
- Run from repository root (where `generate-file-structure.php` lives).
- PHP CLI and PowerShell available (Windows).
- Working copy of `test/` is authoritative.

Quick steps (copy/paste):

1) Export `test/` file list (relative paths)

```powershell
$src = "C:\xampp\htdocs\mlhuillier\test"
Push-Location "C:\xampp\htdocs\mlhuillier"
Get-ChildItem -Path $src -Recurse -File | ForEach-Object {
  $p = $_.FullName.Substring($src.Length+1).TrimStart('\'); $p -replace '\\','/'
} | Sort-Object > test-files.txt
Pop-Location
```

2) Extract scaffolder template keys and write them to disk for comparison

```powershell
Push-Location "C:\xampp\htdocs\mlhuillier"
php -r '
$tpl = include "generate-file-structure.php";
foreach($tpl as $k=>$v){
  $path = "scaffold_templates/".ltrim($k,"/");
  @mkdir(dirname($path), 0777, true);
  file_put_contents($path, $v);
}
echo "Wrote scaffold_templates/";'
Pop-Location
```

3) Produce path-level report: missing in scaffold, extra in scaffold

```powershell
$test = Get-Content test-files.txt
$scaffold = Get-ChildItem -Recurse -File scaffold_templates | ForEach-Object{
  $_.FullName.Substring((Get-Location).Path.Length+1) -replace '\\','/'
} | Sort-Object
# Missing in scaffold:
Compare-Object -ReferenceObject $test -DifferenceObject $scaffold | Where-Object { $_.SideIndicator -eq "<=" } | ForEach-Object { "MISSING-IN-SCAFFOLD: $($_.InputObject)" }
# Extra in scaffold:
Compare-Object -ReferenceObject $test -DifferenceObject $scaffold | Where-Object { $_.SideIndicator -eq "=>" } | ForEach-Object { "EXTRA-IN-SCAFFOLD: $($_.InputObject)" }
```

4) Content diffs for matching paths (produces unified diff files)

```powershell
$baseTest = "C:\xampp\htdocs\mlhuillier\test"
$baseScaffold = "C:\xampp\htdocs\mlhuillier\scaffold_templates"
New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path diffs | Out-Null
foreach($rel in (Get-ChildItem $baseTest -Recurse -File | ForEach-Object { $_.FullName.Substring($baseTest.Length+1) -replace '\\','/' })){
  $a = Join-Path $baseTest ($rel -replace '/','\\')
  $b = Join-Path $baseScaffold ($rel -replace '/','\\')
  if(Test-Path $b){
    if((Get-Content $a -Raw) -ne (Get-Content $b -Raw)){
      Write-Output "DIFF: $rel"
      $safe = $rel -replace '/','__'
      fc $a $b | Out-File -FilePath (Join-Path 'diffs' ($safe + '.diff')) -Encoding utf8
    }
  }
}
```

5) Generate a temp project to validate generator output (optional)

```powershell
$target = "C:\xampp\htdocs\mlhuillier\mirror-temp"
Remove-Item -Recurse -Force $target -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
php generate-file-structure.php create mirror-temp
```

6) Remediation guidance (how to fix mismatches)
- If `MISSING-IN-SCAFFOLD: path`: add a new key in `generate-file-structure.php` with that relative path and the file content as a heredoc.
- If `DIFF: path`: inspect the `diffs/` file and update the scaffolder template to match `test/` (preferred).

7) Re-run generator + verify
- Run `php generate-file-structure.php create <projectName>` and re-run the comparison steps.

8) Optional final step — sync served project
- To immediately fix a live project (e.g., `del`):

```powershell
robocopy C:\xampp\htdocs\mlhuillier\test C:\xampp\htdocs\del /MIR /COPY:DAT /R:2 /W:1
```

Notes & Best Practices:
- Back up `generate-file-structure.php` before large edits.
- Prefer updating scaffolder templates rather than ad-hoc generated projects.
- Keep `scaffold_templates/` and `diffs/` for audit history and CI checks.

